Start 

Main Module 

    Connect to the students database 

    Create the table if it does not already exist 

  

    While user does not choose to quit 

        Display menu 

        Get user choice  

  

        If selection is 1 then 

            Call Display_Records 

        Else If selection is 2 then 

            Call Edit_Record 

        Else If selection is 3 then 

            Exit loop 

        End If 

    End While 

  

    Close the database connection 

End Module 

  

  

Module Display_Records 

    Execute SQL command to select all records from Students table 

    For each record returned 

        Display Student ID 

        Display Student Name

        Display address 

        Display major 

        Display GPA 

        Display email 

        Display phone number 

        Display Favorite Food

        Display a blank line 

    End For 

End Module 

  

  

Module Edit_Record 

    Call Display_Records 

    Ask user to enter the ID of the record to edit 

    Get recordID 

  

    Execute SQL command to retrieve the record with the matching ID 

  

    If no record is found then 

        Display "Record not found." 

        Return to mainline 

    End If 

  

    Display current field values 

    Ask user which field to change: 

        1. Student ID

        2. Name 

        3. Address 

        4. Major 

        5. GPA 

        6. Email 

        7. Phone Number 

        8. Favorite Food 

        9. Cancel 

    Get choice 

  

    If choice is between 1 and 7 then 

        Ask user for the new value 

        Get newValue 

        Build SQL UPDATE command using newValue and recordID 

        Execute SQL UPDATE command 

        Display "Record updated." 

    Else 

        Display "Edit canceled." 

    End If 

End Module 

  

  

Module Display_Menu 

    Display "1. Display All Student Records" 

    Display "2. Edit a Student Record" 

    Display "3. Quit" 

End Module 
